modules.description: Sets up a test runner that attaches to the document's onLoad event and executes test suites, outputting results to stdout with optional color formatting. Works with test suite structures defined in Webtest.Suite. Used to initialize and trigger browser-based test execution during page load.

Provides assertion functions for testing JavaScript values, including equality checks, exception handling, and test case grouping. Works with primitive types, arrays, and objects exposed through js_of_ocaml. Enables writing and running tests directly in the browser to validate client-side JavaScript logic.

provides a test execution framework that runs test suites defined in Webtest.Suite, attaching to the document's onLoad event and printing results to stdout with optional color. It supports structured test organization and automated execution in a browser environment. Operations include test suite registration, execution, and result reporting. Example tasks include running a suite of unit tests or integrating with a CI pipeline for browser-based validation.
